article.headline: Quinnipiac 59, Albany (NY) 57
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Ike Azotam scored 17 points, hitting the game-winning jumper with 14 seconds left to give Quinnipiac a 59-57 victory over Albany (N.Y.) on Friday night. The Bobcats (4-6), who trailed 57-52 with 3:43 remaining, scored the last seven points to snap the Great Danes' six-game winning streak. Zaid Hearst started the spurt with a 3-pointer with 2:32 to go, then Jamee Jackson's jumper tied it with 1:44 left. After Azotam's shot, Albany called a time out, then Mike Black missed a 3-point attempt with 2 seconds remaining. Quinnipiac led for all but 10 seconds of the first half, though the Great Danes scored five straight points to trail 26-24 at the break. Albany (9-3) got within a point three times in the second half before pulling ahead with an 8-0 run, capped by Black's 3-pointer making it 42-38 with 10:16 left. Sam Rowley scored 15 and Black 14 for Albany.
